    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Using `:set writedelay=10` and then calling `:redraw!` cannot be canceled using `Ctrl-c`: Neovim will stop the delayed redrawing, but appears to still apply the delays, i.e. it takes a while until the screen is updated and it accepts input again.\r\nVim behaves better in this regard.\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.2.3-901-ga9c94f7bb",
